Validate identifiers, metadata, and ontology serialization/checks","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Commit only intended changes and create ISSUE_COMMENTS.md and PR_COMMENTS.md","status":"pending","priority":"high"}],"truncated":false},"title":"5 todos","time":{"start":1778981342601,"end":1778981342608}},"id":"prt_e338d06a7001iv5fcPYDXzzkpo","sessionID":"ses_1cc731d29ffeAv83jd6twnaLta","messageID":"msg_e338cf8e7001Qh0iI8esUDlkkb"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778981342802,"sessionID":"ses_1cc731d29ffeAv83jd6twnaLta","part":{"id":"prt_e338cfdc7001PedP60SLpvMnRN","messageID":"msg_e338cf8e7001Qh0iI8esUDlkkb","sessionID":"ses_1cc731d29ffeAv83jd6twnaLta","type":"text","text":"Planning sequence: inspect `__issue_context__.json` and repo instructions, identify whether this is new-term or term-edit work, then use any required validation agents before checkout/edit/checkin. After the ontology change, I’ll validate identifiers/metadata, run the relevant ontology checks, commit only touched ontology files, and leave `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md` and `PR_COMMENTS.md` uncommitted.","time":{"start":1778981338567,"end":1778981342800}}}
