{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778981507017,"sessionID":"ses_1cc731d29ffeAv83jd6twnaLta","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_DWvKRAgy2FXfQ7nG1Hb8iSg0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I moved the two GO/UBERON disjointness axioms out of `uberon-edit.obo` and into the imported OWL component so the OBO serializer no longer creates unlabeled GO term frames in the edit file.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Resolved issue #3651 by moving the two problematic cross-ontology disjointness axioms involving `UBERON:0000001` out of the OBO edit file and into the imported OWL component `src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl`.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+- Removed the serialized ghost term frame for `GO:0005623` from `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Removed the serialized ghost term frame for `GO:0110165` from `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Added equivalent `DisjointClasses` axioms for `GO:0005623` vs `UBERON:0000001` and `GO:0110165` vs `UBERON:0000001` to `src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl`.\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- This preserves the intended semantics of the disjointness axioms.\n+- It avoids the OBO serialization behavior that rewrites the axioms as unlabeled GO frames inside `uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- `disjoint_union_over.owl` is already imported by `uberon-edit.obo`, so this is the smallest change that keeps the axioms active while preventing the edit-file error.\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+- Re-serialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo -o src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Reviewed the resulting diff to confirm that only the two ghost GO frames were removed from the edit file and the two OWL axioms were added to the component.\n+\n+Completed checklist:\n+- [x] Read issue context and repo guidance.\n+- [x] Confirmed the current problematic serialized GO frames in `uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- [x] Moved the disjointness axioms to an imported OWL component.\n+- [x] Re-serialized the edit file.\n+- [x] Verified the final diff is limited to the intended ontology changes.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I moved the two GO/UBERON disjointness axioms out of `uberon-edit.obo` and into the imported OWL component so the OBO serializer no longer creates unlabeled GO term frames in the edit file.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@\n+Resolved issue #3651 by moving the two problematic cross-ontology disjointness axioms involving `UBERON:0000001` out of the OBO edit file and into the imported OWL component `src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl`.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+- Removed the serialized ghost term frame for `GO:0005623` from `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Removed the serialized ghost term frame for `GO:0110165` from `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Added equivalent `DisjointClasses` axioms for `GO:0005623` vs `UBERON:0000001` and `GO:0110165` vs `UBERON:0000001` to `src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl`.\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- This preserves the intended semantics of the disjointness axioms.\n+- It avoids the OBO serialization behavior that rewrites the axio